  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\">The summoner may cast a spell with a target of &ldquo;you&rdquo; on his eidolon (as a spell with a range of touch) instead of on himself. A summoner may cast spells on his eidolon even if the spells normally do not affect creatures of the eidolon's type (outsider). </span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\">Spells cast in this way must come from the summoner spell list. </span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\">This ability does not allow the eidolon to share abilities that are not spells, even if they function like spells.</span></p>",
